events.name: Golden State Warriors at LA Clippers

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry is among the most dangerous players in the NBA. But an angry Curry proved to be more lethal.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry has 33 points, Warriors beat Clippers for 8th straight

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 26 points and 13 rebounds and the Milwaukee Bucks extended their winning streak to seven, routing the Indiana Pacers 118-100 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Defending champ Bucks rout Pacers for 7th straight win

headlines.description: — Marcus Smart scored 21 points, Al Horford had 17 points and 11 rebounds and the Boston Celtics beat the short-handed Toronto Raptors 109-97 on Sunday night to snap a two-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics beat short-handed Raptors for 4th win in 6 games

headlines.description: — Dillon Brooks scored 21 points, Desmond Bane added 18 and the Memphis Grizzlies took advantage of Sacramento’s poor shooting to beat the Kings 128-101 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brooks, Bane lead Grizzlies past poor-shooting Kings

events.name: Detroit Pistons at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James and Isaiah Stewart had no Round 2 in the Lakers' rematch with the Pistons.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron has 33 points, Lakers beat Pistons in calm rematch
